The division problem given to Fritz is \(\frac{a}{b}\). Fritz calculates \(a=57 \cdot b+52\), performs the check, and gets \(57 \cdot b^{\prime}+52=17380\), where the factor \(b^{\prime}\) differs from the correct value \(b\) by the tens digit.

