The sequence \(a_{n}\) is strictly monotonically decreasing if and only if the sequence \(b_{n}=a_{n}-\frac{7}{10}\) is also. Here,

\[
\begin{gathered}
b_{n}=\sqrt{25 n^{2}+7 n+1}-\left(5 n+\frac{7}{10}\right) \\
=\frac{\left(\sqrt{25 n^{2}+7 n+1}-\left(5 n+\frac{7}{10}\right)\right) \cdot\left(\sqrt{25 n^{2}+7 n+1}+5 n+\frac{7}{10}\right)}{\sqrt{25 n^{2}+7 n+1}+5 n+\frac{7}{10}}=\frac{\left(25 n^{2}+7 n+1\right)-\left(5 n+\frac{7}{10}\right)^{2}}{\sqrt{25 n^{2}+7 n+1}+5 n+\frac{7}{10}} \\
=\frac{\left(25 n^{2}+7 n+1\right)-\left(25 n^{2}+7 n+\frac{49}{100}\right)}{\sqrt{25 n^{2}+7 n+1}+5 n+\frac{7}{10}} \\
=\frac{\frac{51}{100}}{\sqrt{25 n^{2}+7 n+1}+5 n+\frac{7}{10}}
\end{gathered}
\]

Since the numerator of this fraction is constant, while the denominator is a strictly monotonically increasing function in \(n\), the sequence \(b_{n}\) - and thus also the sequence \(a_{n}\) - is strictly monotonically decreasing. Furthermore, for all \(n\), the numerator and denominator of \(b_{n}\) are clearly positive, so for all \(n\), \(b_{n}>0\) and \(a_{n}=b_{n}+\frac{7}{10}>\frac{7}{10}\).

